
[1]mithridate

   MITH'RIDATE, n. In pharmacy, an antidote against poison, or a
   composition in form of an electuary, supposed to serve either as a
   remedy or a preservative against poison. It takes its name from
   Mithridates, king of Pontus, the inventor.
